cosine similarity function

cos(d,q) = sum(di * qi)/(sqrt(sum di^2)*sqrt(sum qi^2))

pearson formula

(sum(di - da) * sum(qi - qa))/sqrt(sum (di-da)^2)*sqrt(sum (qi-qa)^2))

Key
di = score of item reviewed by d
qi = score of same item reviewed by q

da = average score from d
qa = average score from q

